1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §3174-PPP is enacted to read:
3 §3174-PPP. Reimbursement for doula services
4 1. Definition. For purposes of this section, "doula services" means the provision of
5 services to a person by a nonclinical professional related to the physical, emotional and
6 informational support of that person throughout pregnancy, labor, birth and the postpartum
7 period, including, but not limited to, guidance and support concerning pregnancy health,
8 childbirth, infant feeding and newborn care.
9 2. Reimbursement. Beginning January 1, 2026, the department shall provide
10 reimbursement under the MaineCare program for doula services, including, but not limited
11 to, attendance during childbirth and a maximum of 4 prenatal and 4 postpartum visits.
12 3. Advisory committee. The department shall establish a doula advisory committee
13 to provide advice and make recommendations to the department regarding doula services.
14 The advisory committee must include practicing doulas and must represent a range of
15 experience levels. Advice provided by the advisory committee must include, but is not
16 limited to, the scope of doula services eligible for reimbursement under this section, the
17 recruitment of a diverse workforce of doulas to provide services in the State, the
18 development of comprehensive continuing education and training at low cost,
19 reimbursement billing issues, outreach to the public about how to access doula services and
20 maintaining a reimbursement rate for doula services that incentivizes and supports a diverse
21 workforce.
22 4. Rulemaking. The department shall adopt rules to implement this section. Rules
23 adopted pursuant to this subsection are routine technical rules as defined by Title 5, chapter
24 375, subchapter 2‑A.
25 SUMMARY
2266 This bill requires reimbursement under the MaineCare program for doula services. It
2277 also requires the Department of Health and Human Services to establish an advisory
2288 committee to provide advice and make recommendations to the department regarding doula
2299 services.
